INTRODUCTION
------------

"Oh no.... no player again ! I have so many of them on my harddisk and the
most are trash........"

So or similiar many peoples will say if they get this program in their hands.
They are right i said but this player is not made for everybody.
I will tell the short story of this player and what i want to do with it in
the further:

In the winter of 1995 i decided to write a moduleplayer for the PC. I never
wrote something like sound and i (and the whole group) needed it for our
first demo. So i started to handle some infos of programing the Soundblaster.
I was doing my military service in germany at this time and lot of free time
wanted to be used for. I'm was working in a bureau in the Prinz-Eugen-Kaserne
in Traunstein and i only went home at weekend.
After 1 week i managed to put some VOCs out of my SB 2.5 and i was proud. :)
I met two guys there, also PC freaks: Jakl and Lost
There were very interested of my project and they helped me to discuss many
thinks about it. Jakl started to write an surface for this player and i started
after many theorie thinking and a lot of paper to code the player.
I started to write it in Borland C++ 3.1, only for testing it. After christmas
and the "New Year" the C player managed to play a 6 channel S3M on my Pentium.
Not fast but OK. I used S3M cause it was my favorit format and quite simple.
After some theortically thinking i started in februar 1996 to write my player
in assembler, a hard work to do !
After 2 weeks the player was started the first time, and played a 16 channel
S3M without problems. The player could only play 8 bit and mono and used EMS.
The next weeks more effekts were included and the player was optimized.
In april the player was about two times faster than the first one and the most
important effects were included. I changed the memory model in 32bit flat
memory model where also memory above 1meg could be used directly. But this
forbid the EMM386 managers cause of protected mode programming. :(
After one week and lots of new info of SB programming i started to write the
player to handle 16 bit too. (i buyed a SB16 ASP a few weeks before :)
This was v0.10ŕ and i spread it for testing to my friends.
In the 30 june i left the militair cause in november studiing will start.

I don't want this player is like the others. The highest priority is quality
and no graphic effekts.
This player is and will be written in first case for the demo scene.
And YOU will "write" it ! Not personaly but you will give help and advise to
make this player to what YOU want. Many little demo-groups have no "good"
player and search for one (i was asked several times) and this is what i want
to do. Give people the OBJ to include it in their own demos and give ASM
source codes to show and learn other people how to program a player.
This is the idea of the demo-scene not like so many lamers who don't want
to give some source to other people, protecting their source like a secret,
even when it is several years old !! If you don't give it to other, you don't
give them a chance in the demo-scene, probably frightend of be better than
you ? Every demo must be better then the last one and it is more and more
difficult for newcomers to get IN the scene. (Greets to Hydra :)





